What you need to know:

Kenya Wildlife Service for instance recorded a deficit of Sh680.52 million during 2016/17 financial year.A task force on State corporations chaired by former Mandera Central MP Abdikadir Mohamed recommended merging of some parastatals, including the perennial loss-making ones.In the 2015/16 financial year, the Kenya Veterinary Board made a loss of Sh12.94 million.